Docs.summary: Any predicate expression wrapped in this will be ignored for specialization.
Docs.remarks: This is useful for when you need to add expression to the trigger that are part of rule mechanics rather than of intent. For example, if you have a counter for how often a particular message is displayed, then that is part of the triggering condition, but all such rules would be incomparable because they counter is per-rule.

When an expression is being processed, optional creates a disjunction where the expression is both included and not included with the rest of the expression. This is a simple way to express this common relationship. By generating both clauses then matching the expression can be more specific when the optional expression is true.
